      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For the press statement, it's often best to use careful, non-alarmist language instead of immediately calling it a \"breach.\" You can describe it as an \"unauthorized disclosure\" or an \"incident involving limited user data.\" Focus the narrative on what you are doing to secure the system and what specific steps you are taking to support those affected users immediately. Transparency about the small scope helps mitigate panic and maintains professional control.",
